Charlie Kirk embodied courage in defending free expression and open dialogue, principles at the very heart of our democracy. His unwavering commitment reminded us that America’s strength comes from the freedom to speak, debate, and engage openly, even when we disagree.

Today, we remember his life and proudly honor the legacy he leaves behind, a legacy that challenges us to continue safeguarding the values he so boldly championed.

Cheering loud for our UM today! No better stage than Miami to show the pride and spirit of the Canes. 

Orange. Green. Glory. 🍊🏈

Just as I saw you lead with courage in the House and during our time together on the Foreign Affairs Committee, I know you’ll represent America’s values with strength on the world stage at the UN!

Mantener abierto a nuestro gobierno fue lo correcto, para Miami y para Estados Unidos. Estoy comprometida a trabajar con mis colegas para aprobar un año completo de asignaciones que apoyen a nuestras familias, a nuestros negocios y a nuestra comunidad.

¡La Era Dorada ya está aquí! 🇺🇸

Keeping our government open was the right thing to do, for Miami and for America. I’m committed to working with my colleagues to deliver a full year of appropriations that supports our families, businesses, and community.

The Golden Age is here! 🇺🇸

Charlie Kirk defendió sin miedo la libertad de expresión y el debate honesto, valores que hacen grande a EE.UU. y que debemos defender siempre, incluso en los pasillos del Congreso.

Hoy es un honor votar por la resolución que celebra su vida, su legado y su lucha inquebrantable por nuestra Nación. 🇺🇸

Charlie Kirk was a fearless champion for free speech and honest debate, values that define America and must always be defended, especially in the halls of Congress.

Today, it is my honor to vote for the resolution celebrating his life, his legacy, and his unwavering fight for the principles that make this Nation great.

Orgullosa de anunciar importantes avances en mis prioridades legislativas en el Comité de Asuntos Exteriores de la Cámara:

1️⃣ Ley para Proteger la Democracia Hondureña – Asegura la supervisión de EE. UU. en las elecciones del 30 de noviembre en Honduras para evitar fraudes de los Zelaya.

2️⃣ Ley para Restaurar la Soberanía y los Derechos Humanos en Nicaragua – Revisa el CAFTA-DR, respalda a los grupos que luchan contra Ortega y lo enfrenta en la ONU.

3️⃣ Reducción de Tiempos de Espera para Visas – Obliga a que el 80 % de los solicitantes tengan su entrevista en un máximo de 3 semanas.

Han pasado más de 20 años desde la última vez que se reautorizó el presupuesto del Departamento de Estado. Es un trabajo arduo, pero esencial para mantener el liderazgo de Estados Unidos.

Proud to report progress on my legislative priorities in tonight’s House Foreign Affairs Committee:

1️⃣Protect Honduran Democracy Act – Ensures U.S. monitoring of Honduras’ Nov. 30 elections to prevent fraud by the Zelayas.

 2️⃣Restoring Sovereignty & Human Rights in Nicaragua Act – Reviews CAFTA-DR, supports anti-Ortega groups, and counters Ortega at the U.N.

 3️⃣Reduced Visa Wait Times – Requires 80% of applicants to get interviews within 3 weeks.

We haven’t reauthorized State’s budget since 2002. It’s tedious, but vital for America’s leadership. 🇺🇸

Hoy, junto a mis colegas @MarioDB y @RepCarlos , participé en una videoconferencia sobre las tropas cubanas enviadas a pelear por Rusia en la guerra contra Ucrania.

La dictadura cubana siempre se ha enriquecido tratando a su pueblo como mercancía: primero médicos, ahora soldados. ¡Debemos detenerlos!

Ukrainian intelligence confirmed to us that thousands of young Cubans are being forced to fight for Russia. Given Putin’s desire to hire “expendable” soldiers, the Regime is making MILLIONS by sending their own youth to an early grave.

The Cuban dictatorship has always gotten rich by treating their people as commodities, first doctors, now soldiers. They must be stopped!

My proposed PANA Act amendment just passed unanimously in the Foreign Affairs Committee markup tonight! 

PANA would turn stolen money into a tool for Venezuela’s freedom, allowing us to use the nearly 4 BILLION dollars we’ve seized from drug traffickers and criminals connected to Chavez and Maduro and invest it in a democratic Venezuela. 

This is how we can begin to rebuild Venezuela after decades of devastation!

Orgullosa de estar entre los congresistas que lideraron hoy el esfuerzo en @HouseForeignGOP y @HouseForeign para la reautorización del Departamento de Estado.

Con el proyecto de ley H.R. 5426 y la enmienda que propuse, aseguramos que puestos clave del Departamento de Estado queden establecidos por ley, restaurando el orden en la agencia que dirige nuestra diplomacia en el mundo.

La supervisión federal es uno de nuestros poderes constitucionales más importantes, y el resultado de este trabajo bipartidista significa un Departamento de Estado más fuerte y una América más fuerte. 🇺🇸

Proud to be part of the members leading  the charge at today’s @HouseForeignGOP @HouseForeign State Department Reauthorization markup.

H.R. 5426 and the Manager’s amendment I proposed today finally puts key positions at State into law to restore order to the agency leading our Diplomacy abroad. 

Federal oversight is one of our most important Constitutional powers, and the result of our bipartisan work will mean a stronger State Department and a stronger America! 👇

https://t.co/1HxTQ3MOaP

Me alegra que la Reserva Federal finalmente haya reducido las tasas de interés.

Esta decisión fortalecerá nuestra economía, generará nuevas oportunidades y ayudará a impulsar la próxima era dorada de Estados Unidos. 🇺🇸
I’m glad the Federal Reserve finally cut rates. This decision will strengthen our economy, create new opportunities, and help fuel America’s next Golden Age. 🇺🇸

Miami’s future depends on smart, proactive policy. The Terrorism Risk Insurance Act (TRIA) isn’t just an abstract program, it safeguards our schools, hospitals, and neighborhoods. I’m glad the Committee is treating this issue with the urgency it deserves, and I strongly support reauthorizing this critical protection.

For me, this is especially important because the University of Miami, right in my district, relies on TRIA to secure affordable coverage for its hospitals, research facilities, and stadiums. Without it, both the University and the broader Miami community would be left vulnerable to devastating losses.

Welcome to America’s newest citizens! It’s the honor of a lifetime, especially on Constitution Day.

Today you join the greatest club in the world, one forged in freedom and sustained by the courage of those who came before us. 🇺🇸

This nation, its laws, and its traditions are now yours to cherish and protect. Congratulations!

Financial predators are stealing from Florida’s seniors. Not on my watch! 

This week, I’m backing the Financial Exploitation Prevention Act, giving firms the power to freeze suspicious withdrawals, protect retirement savings, and shut down these thieves once and for all.

Florida’s seniors have earned peace of mind, and I’ll make sure they get it.

This month we celebrate the Hispanic community and their integral place in America’s tapestry of cultures. 

As the proud daughter of Cuban exiles defined by my Hispanic culture grounded in faith, family, freedom and hard-work, I’ll always keep fighting so every family can thrive in the land of opportunity.

Por eso seguiré luchando en el Congreso para que cada familia hispana pueda prosperar y alcanzar el Sueño Americano en esta tierra de oportunidades.

Charlie Kirk died a hero. He was a true warrior, assassinated for his ideas and for fighting for what he believed in.

We didn’t agree on everything, but in America no one should ever be targeted for their beliefs.

He spent his life teaching young people on campuses, daring them to be different, to be rebels through conservatism.

We will never forget his legacy, and we will never let violence silence us, or prevail. Rest in peace, Charlie. May your soul find eternal peace.
I am shocked and horrified by the news of Charlie Kirk being shot and I am praying for him and his family.

This term, I’m proud to co-sponsor the SAVES Act (HR 2605) to provide better care for veterans with PTSD. 

We honor the brave men and women who’ve worn the uniform and we commit to ensuring none of them ever fight their battles alone. 

In Congress and beyond, I’ll never stop working to protect those who once protected us.

On #WorldSuicidePreventionDay, I am reaffirming my commitment to making sure no one battles alone.

In my first term, I led the Summer Barrow Act, now law, to address mental health and substance abuse issues. 

We can help in Congress, and I will continue to always do my part on this important issue.

Hoy en el Comité de Servicios Financieros le pedí a la directora de FinCEN que investigue a compañías del sur de la Florida que estarían violando el embargo y financiando la dictadura cubana.

También le pedí a la administración Trump castigar a toda empresa que ayude al régimen. Cada dólar que evade sanciones alimenta la represión en La Habana y le roba la libertad al pueblo cubano.

Today at the House Financial Services Committee, I asked FinCEN Director Andrea Gacki to look into companies in South Florida allegedly violating the Cuban embargo and channeling American dollars into the dictatorship’s machinery of oppression.

In a recent letter, I urged the Trump administration to take one clear step: punish any company that helps the Cuban regime.

No one should profit from tyranny. Every dollar that evades sanctions doesn’t just pad the regime’s pockets, it fuels Havana’s oppression and robs the Cuban people of their freedom.

The people of Miami carry the deep scars of communism in their hearts.

Just ask our Venezuelan exile community, forced to flee their homeland after thugs like Maduro stole their freedom.

That’s why I support @POTUS standing up to Maduro and his narco-terrorist allies. Communism and its tyrants must be crushed wherever they try to rise.

This is incorrect.

This is a provision from the Dream Act included in the bill. No criminals or gang members are eligible. Period. 

Here’s how it works — when a Dreamer would apply to adjust status, there is an investigation - including a criminal background check, check for gang affiliation, and more. 

During that investigation, the federal and state gang database network can absolutely be a factor in determining gang membership, but the presence on a list alone does not disqualify them immediately.

There must be another factor to prove gang membership - which could be a criminal charge (not just conviction), tattoos, gang dress, evidence from law enforcement investigations, social media, witness testimony, prison records, etc. 

Also, the burden is on the Dreamer to prove they qualify for adjusted status - so if they are on a database (or not on a database, but there is other proof of gang membership), they have to prove that is incorrect. 

This is because the gang databases have proven inaccurate in federal courts. 

Just like many who have found themselves incorrectly flagged on a database - NICS (gun purchases), No Fly list, etc - when they shouldn’t be. 

So when it comes to gang membership, it means — Gang database + another factor. 

That’s it - simple. Not a smoking gun.
